webpackJsonp([1815],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/articles-certificates-use-the-bootstrap-grid-to-put-elements-side-by-side.json":function(e,s){e.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Bootstrap uses a responsive grid system that makes it easier to put elements into rows and tell each element\'s relative width.</p>\n<div class="lightbox-wrapper">[![Bootstrap 12 column grid layout](https://www.evernote.com/shard/s116/sh/f0944d97-08b8-4615-8273-a327bf41fb05/de1a3acbceef89ae/deep/0/)\n<div class="meta"><span class="filename">0</span><span class="informations">901x348</span><span class="expand"></span></div>](https://www.evernote.com/shard/s116/sh/f0944d97-08b8-4615-8273-a327bf41fb05/de1a3acbceef89ae/deep/0/ "0") </div>\n<p>Note that in this illustration, the <code>col-md-_</code> class is being used. Here, md means medium, and _ is a number specifying how many columns wide the element should be. In this case, the column width of an element on a medium-sized screen, such as a laptop, is being specified.</p>\n<pre><code>&#x3C;div class="row">\n\n  &#x3C;div class="col-xs-4">&#x3C;button class="btn btn-block btn-primary">Like&#x3C;/button>&#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;div class="col-xs-4">&#x3C;button class="btn btn-block btn-info">Info&#x3C;/button>&#x3C;/div>\n  &#x3C;div class="col-xs-4">&#x3C;button class="btn btn-block btn-danger">Delete&#x3C;/button>&#x3C;/div>\n\n&#x3C;/div>\n</code></pre>',frontmatter:{title:"Use the Bootstrap Grid To Put Elements Side By Side",parent:"/home/stuart/guides/src/pages/articles/certificates/use-the-bootstrap-grid-to-put-elements-side-by-side/index.md absPath of file"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/articles/certificates/use-the-bootstrap-grid-to-put-elements-side-by-side/"}}}});
